# GTA-RBS API documentation index

This directory holds API and CLI documentation for RBS (Key Broker Service) and RBC (Key Broker Client). **The authoritative spec is [rbs.yaml](./rbs.yaml)** (OpenAPI 3.0); Markdown docs are human-readable narrative and examples, kept in sync with rbs.yaml—in case of conflict, rbs.yaml wins.

## Documents and audience

| Document | Description | Audience |
|----------|-------------|----------|
| [rbs_api.md](./rbs_api.md) | RBS REST API: auth, resources, Admin, config, system, error codes | Server dev, integrators |
| [rbs.yaml](./rbs.yaml) | OpenAPI 3.0 spec, machine-readable full API definition | Codegen, automation, authoritative spec |
| [rbc_interface.md](./rbc_interface.md) | RBC client interface: C (sync/async callback), Rust (sync/async), CLI subset | Client/embedded dev, SDK implementers |
| [rbs_cli.md](./rbs_cli.md) | rbs-cli: token, user, client, policy and resource management subcommands | Ops, scripts, manual use |

## Recommended reading order

- **Server / integrating with RBS**: read [rbs_api.md](./rbs_api.md) first, then [rbs.yaml](./rbs.yaml) as needed.
- **Client / embedding RBC**: read [rbc_interface.md](./rbc_interface.md) first; it depends on auth and resource semantics in [rbs_api.md](./rbs_api.md).
- **Ops / scripts**: use [rbs_cli.md](./rbs_cli.md); the client subcommand matches the CLI section of [rbc_interface.md](./rbc_interface.md).

## Versioning and sync

- Docs and rbs.yaml share the same version (e.g. 0.1.0). When the API changes, update rbs.yaml and the corresponding Markdown together and keep paths, methods, status codes, and error bodies consistent.
